 11  # Semiconjugate elements of a semigroup
 12  
 13  ## Main definitions
 14  
 15  We say that `x` is semiconjugate to `y` by `a` (`semiconj_by a x y`), if `a * x = y * a`.
 16  In this file we  provide operations on `semiconj_by _ _ _`.
 17  
 18  In the names of these operations, we treat `a` as the “left” argument,
 19  and both `x` and `y` as “right” arguments. This way most names in this
 20  file agree with the names of the corresponding lemmas for `commute a b
 21  = semiconj_by a b b`. As a side effect, some lemmas have only `_right`
 22  version.
 23  
 24  Lean does not immediately recognise these terms as equations,
 25  so for rewriting we need syntax like `rw [(h.pow_right 5).eq]`
 26  rather than just `rw [h.pow_right 5]`.
 27  -/
 28  
 29  universes u v
 30  
 31  open_locale smul
 32  
 33  /-- `x` is semiconjugate to `y` by `a`, if `a * x = y * a`. -/
 34  def semiconj_by {M : Type u} [has_mul M] (a x y : M) : Prop := a * x = y * a
id                                 └─────┘ ┴           ┴            ┴ ┴ ┴ ┴ ┴ ┴ ┴
src                                └─────┘                            ┴   ┴   ┴
typ                                └─────┘ ┴           ┴            ┴ ┴ ┴ ┴ ┴ ┴ ┴
